I hope that everyone can see what an amazing group of professionals they are.

author: @dearmliz
text:
I see this on other videos but not here, so my contribution to new carats!

(in order of appearance from song starting (aka not including their awesome intro):
Joshua (Hong Jisoo 🦌or🐰) 0:42 - center, lead vocalist, a sunday morning latte of confidence and assurance
Hoshi (Kwon Soonyoung 🐯) 0:56  - lead dancer and leader of performance unit, obsessed with tigers forever pure
Woozi (Lee Jihoon 🍚 ) 1:06 - trifecta of perfection aka producer of 99% of their songs, buff king, leader of vocal unit
Wonwoo (Jeon Wonwoo 😼) 1:15 - lead rapper, a perfect snack of calm and wit
Mingyu (Kim Mingyu 🐶 ) 1:20 - lead rapper, puppy dog eyes and brand ambassador for everything luxurious
DK or Dokyeom (Lee Seokmin ⚔) 1:26 - lead vocal, eternal sunshine and lover of the small things in life
Seungkwan (Boo Seungkwan 🍊) 1:36 - lead vocal, baby of Jeju and literally the entertainment industry's blessing
S.Coups (Choi Seungcheol 🍒) 1:43 - SVT and carat's leader, lead rapper, competition's  biggest threat and struggler of realizing just how wonderful he is
Dino (Lee Chan 🦕) 1:49 -  maknae, lead dancer who thrives off bettering himself and understanding those around him, the least maknae of maknaes ever
Jeonghan (Yoon Jeonghan 👼 ) 1:56 - lead vocalist, angel with a dual edge sword (loves being competitive and joking around with members)
The8 (Xu Minghao 🐸) 1:59 - lead dancer, assertively chic and forever at peace... his self confidence and assurance forever astounds us
Jun (Moon Junhui 😺) 2:16 - lead dancer, funniest despite being one of the quietest of group, quick in wit but permanently perplexed trying to understand those around him
Vernon (Chwe Hansol 🎸or🤘) 2:28 - lead rapper, co-producer of many songs, introverted music geek with a profound outlook on life, responsible and so very loveable

WELCOME TO THE DIAMOND LIFE, and STREAM HOT and _WORLD !!
*edit to clarify -- Wonwoo has a smirking cat face, Jun has a regular cat face :)

author: @bunny3471
text:
Ok we all agreed every second of this mv is the killing part..

And here is what's my opinion the highlights:
- I totally agrees with this hyung line settings (it starts with joshua, ends with jeonghan, scoup the ending fairy) perfectly nice.
-  0:44  I don't know why every time it starts with shua, I feel like it gives clarity and peaceful vibe start to the MV, if that make sense🤣  its like when you eat a cake, the first bite affects the impression of the whole, when the first start is nice you would less likely doubts the bites that came after. 😅😅 What I meant to say was: your a great flavour that complete the seventeen cake.❤️❤️❤️
- the hip-hop team becomes vocalist in this mv except scoup where he *kill the rap part perfectly*.
- 0:00-0:34 let us all appreciate these sport magazine top-tier visual models..
- 1:57  hannie and his fav baby moments, "dino, nugu aegi?"
- 2:10  dino collecting his hyung to formation with dinosaur stomps 
- 2:43  angelic vocals duo.

vocal team: perfect harmony- the main flavours of the song:
-  1:06  woozi ✨everything about him here is just too beautiful, like his hair, his style, his movement, *Everything*, like *this is his era*, this is his best hair style and colour for me it suits him so so well, like an anime character hdjshdjhdhd. Ok I'll stop. 
- DK yg bae❤️ heart and center stealer as always, drop dead angelic vocals. 2:57 my fav part.
- seungkwan baby, drop dead angelic vocals duo. so stable vocal✨✨
- jeonghannie,  here your vocals come off strong and Im loving it..always and always will love your voice. (and every hairstyle you pull ) 
- joshua, your soft angelic voice is such a blessing..

The hip-hop team: ✨slaying the vocals✨:
-  1: 16  meanie, vocalist here I see (and also the visual duo 👀👀) one after another, Beautiful, Perfectly Beautiful.
-  2:27  vernom, your vocals are top notch!! The facial expressions was *full of emotions*👀
-  1:43   scoup, you just..just..wow..like...I can't...I just...it was just..*chef kiss*


performance team: stealing the show
-  0:57  hoshi🐯 I swear every time this man moves it's an work of art❤️ I'm so addicted to your moves, it's sooo pationate and full of energy..hwaranghae!!!!
- minghau 👀sir you look stunning here, 0:32 the cold and cool vibe suits you so well and 3:01 YEZZZ
- Jun, you slay!!!!!!! hdgxhsjh 2:17  your lead Dance moves truly reminded us why you belong in the performance team.
- dino, look at youuu jgfkhfjkgkhg  always love your fresh and clear vocals and refine dance moves

author: @nin111dita
text: 5 months ago i had my semester exams going and i had to prepare for exams regarding my job i was sooo under pressure and didn't know how to deal with all the stress.. i used to come here time to time because this song calmed my nerves like nothing else... eventhough i didn't understand the lyrics or meaning of the song the words " We make the rules" always motivated me 😂 today i am here again to say that i got the job i was preparing for and topped my semester exams.. i don't know how i managed to do well in both... but i really thank you Seventeen for being there for me... I dont know whether my message will reach you guys or not but your voices have calmed me and cheered me up during my struggles... author: @lemonysnicket3996
text:
Good day, Carats! Please, let’s stream SEVENTEEN’s mvs! We are literally a big fandom, but why doesn’t we use this power to give back and help SEVENTEEN?

 
What if this would be their last comeback? Their last world tour? And we failed to give them the recognition that they deserved.

 
We need to stream, vote harder, and make sure that SEVENTEEN’s hard work is being paid off. These boys work hard every day for 10+ hours just so they can always provide a high-quality performance but always end up not winning major awards. Seungkwan, DK, and Hoshi always attend variety shows to promote seventeen.

 
These boys never failed to show their appreciation and adoration for us, Carats. I hope we can do the same. :>

 
Streaming their music videos 2x or more a day isn’t that hard. LET’S GO GUYS!!! WE CAN DO IT! YOU CAN DO IT!

Note: I’m sorry, this sounded like a guilt-tripping post. It’s not my intention. Let’s worker harder, Carats!!!

author: @alex-fs9yt
text: This video is shockingly underrated. How can it have only 4.1M views in three months when Ready to Love has 43M views in four months? Even Hoshi and The8's solo tracks have more views than this video, where all members participatd. I know this is labelled a "special video", but why isn't it included in the channel's official music video playlist? It really deserves to be. It may have been filmed all in one place but that shouldn't make it any less of an MV. The song is so good, I can't believe more people haven't heard it. And have you seen the visuals, camera work and choreography?? This definitely serves more views. In my opinion this is one of the best things that happened this year.

author: @헬레몬-e3e
text:
글쓴이는 사전 적힌 글의 내용을 공부한 것은 don't였고 사전에 적힌 글의 내용을 모두 공부하는 것은 빼기하고 살다하였습니다. 그러니까 글쓴이의 언어 표현를 해석하실 때는 사전의 뜻을 빼기하고 해석하세요.

가수였던 세븐틴의 멤버들은 악령을 모르다.가수였던 세븐틴의 멤버들은 강간을 모르다. 가수였던 세븐틴의 멤버들은 윤간은 모르다. 가수였던 세븐틴의 멤버들은 메갈을 모르다. 가수였던 세븐틴의 멤버들은 일진을 모르다. 가수였던 세븐틴의 멤버들은 불(fire)을 모르다.
가수였던 세븐틴의 멤버들은 "나쁘게"를 모르다.

☞모르다의 뜻은 1. 공부한 것 없다. 2. 배우다한 것 없다. 3. 공부한 것 빼기됐다. 4. 배우다한 것 빼기됐다. 

☞없다의 뜻은 숫자0였다. (없다=숫자0) (1-1=숫자0) (100-100=숫자0)

author: @heartsonginfinity2764
text:
I got an F1 2020 ad right after this video which is amusing but more importantly

after watching a bunch of GoSe and silly VLive clips form SVT sometimes I forget that beyond being charismatic comedic and charming in personality they're also fucking phenomenal dancers
like the 95 line will call themselves lazy but that's impossible given how much practice and effort and work goes into getting choreo like this right

The formations are so good, I love how the focus of each line flows so naturally into their center position. Obviously it's one of their most recognized strengths but my God the synchronization. It's incredible that thirteen people of different builds, different heights, can move as one in such a pleasing way to the eye.

Also the visuals hot damn literally everyone looks fine as hell in this 
Special shoutouts to slicked-back black haired, ending fairy S.Coups and form fitting shirt Dino tho 👀👀👀

Anyway tl;dr Racerteen has killed me dead

This era...thank you, boys.

text: I'm freaking loving this!🤩 Badass never looked this cool!🖤 Seventeen as always impresses us by their pure talent but my goodness...this time their stylist needs special appreciation for making them look this ultra chic!😎👍🏻👏

author: @sholjas13
text: Wow 👏👏👏👏👏👏👏👏🏆🥇🥇🥇🥇🥇🥇🥇🥇🥇🥇🥇 Absolutely brilliant ⭐    Just watched it twice and already I could imagine watching it another few times. You got the choreography totally on point. From the all looking good as a group, to the individual minutiae. I love the consistency with your mv's. This track sounds like the summer sunshine gets hotter listening to this. It hit the adrenal glands and excites them beautifully. Brilliant how the Group allow each other's unique vocal range talents exude. As a slight constructive criticism (though I do make this point quite often with various groups), maybe be mindful of the synthesised unison of vocals on the tracks. It does help the polished professional sound, from a Production Team viewpoint, yet the fans love being able to see the Group's development, evolving, improving, learning how to capture our love & our appreciation in the various possibilities with musical arrangements, the songs themselves, the mv's & the complete conceptual profiling as the Group progresses into each new era. Growing with a Group allows the fans' to learn how to appreciate each talented aspect more. Growing up with a favorite Group, enjoying the developments & evolving with the Group(s) is part of the brand marketing that SVT have really got good control of. Fans consistently expect & receive excellent enjoyable entertainment. Maybe be careful that SVT as a Group doesn't loose the ability to input all that individualism that you harness together. Synthesised voices have a tendency to put the control of progress onto the technical staff, who are important yet are not who the fans want to see. Younger generation fans globally may not remember the synthesised songs fading away to non popular. They typically have a 'chosen few' fan base. Look at how the major global artists let their work, their image, & talents, including vocal range, evolve with them & their progress. Even the popularity of genres such as techno, house & garage have peaked & troughed from the use of synthesis. Our human ear gets tired of the humming buzzy sound of synth'd vocals & music. That's part of the evolution of technology. It can't  be human. Natural human evolution is a winning trait that fans understand & relate to. Our listening ears thrive more from human voice, then the fans always remember whose efforts made them feel that much better. 👄😍

author: @mdrdday3987
text:
Selamat malam warga yang budiman. Izinkan saya menyampaikan beberapa apresiasi terhadap video spesial ini. Baik, langsung saja saya paparkan poin-poinnya
1. Terimakasih banyak atas video spesial anyone yang sangat spesial ini
2. Apresiasi tinggi untuk ketampanan, kesempurnaan body, talenta, dan segala yang ada pada diri member. Dengan catatan, semoga kami masih bisa (tetap) waras setelah menonton video ini. 
3. Pengaturan kamera yang sangat istimewa dan sangat keren. Beri applause, terimakasih direktur kamera dan kameramen. 
4. Konsep yang sangat menarik dan unik yang lagi-lagi membuat seventeen lain daripada yang lain. Ga pake mobil ga pake balapan aja udah racing di otak kami, tapi gapapa, kami terima dengan sangat lapang dada. Terimakasih PD-nim. 
5. Outfit yang fashionable abis, yang pastinya sukses membuat carat geger dan jejeritan. Terimakasih untuk tim stylish. 

Mungkin cukup sekian, karena sejujurnya saya sudah speechless dari awal. Saya harap apa yang saya paparkan belum cukup karena betapa berharganya seventeen dan banyaknya yang harus diapresiasi, terimakasih, selamat malam.
